annotationA: Tyrosine-protein kinase Btk29A; Btk family kinase at 29A is a Non-Receptor Tyrosine kinase. Its diverse roles include cellularization, morphogenesis, patterning and germ cell proliferation; Belongs to the protein kinase superfamily. Tyr protein kinase family. TEC subfamily
annotationB: SH3 domain-binding protein 5 homolog; SH3 domain binding; protein kinase inhibitor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: muscle organ development; mesoderm development; negative regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity; muscle cell fate specification; anterior/posterior pattern specification; muscle organ morphogenesis; Belongs to the SH3BP5 family
